14/04/2005
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer told Macedonian Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski that Skopje is making significant progress in defence reforms on its road to NATO integration.
During a meeting in Brussels Wednesday (13 April), he praised the country's participation in international peacekeeping operations.
According to media reports in Skopje, however, the NATO chief also noted concern over the irregularities that emerged in recent municipal elections.
Referring to criticism by the international monitoring mission, de Hoop Scheffer emphasised that a country aspiring to NATO membership must apply the highest elections standards.
(A1 TV, Telma TV - 13/04/05)
